items.name: Security-ML
items.description: This research aims to enhance  cybersecurity by applying advanced  machine learning  techniquesâ€”Random Forest, SVM,  Stacking Classifier, and CNN to  improve threat detection. It will  develop a comprehensive  framework integrating these  methods, assess their performance  across diverse datasets.

items.name: alf-t5
items.description: ALF-T5 - Adaptative Language Framework for T5 is a Machine Learning framework for Neural Machine Translation Systems training and, subsequently, bidirectional translation.

items.name: Credit_Guard
items.description: CreditGuard addresses this  pressing challenge by introducing a data-driven, intelligent risk evaluation system that enhances  the precision of loan default predictions. By leveraging diverse data sources and advanced machine  learning techniques, the project seeks to create a more inclusive and accurate credit assessment  framework.

items.name: Nanofluid-Thermophysical-Property-Prediction_Thermal-Conductivity_Hybrid-ML-DL
items.description: This repository contains code for a comprehensive hybrid machine learning and deep learning frameworks for accurately predicting nanofluid thermal conductivity using stacking ensembles, advanced data augmentation, and metaheuristic optimization techniques.

items.name: Weather-Predictor
items.description: The proposed system introduces a machine learning-based framework for accurate weather prediction, designed to overcome the limitations of traditional forecasting methods. The system focuses on predicting temperature, rainfall, and humidity using historical weather data from NOAA

items.name: Model_Data_Fusion
items.description: An automated machine learning-assisted ensemble framework (AutoML-Ens) for assembling multiple models in geosciences.

items.name: NBTest
items.description: A regression testing framework for Jupyter Notebooks used for Machine Learning tasks

items.name: alpha-regime
items.description: A machine learning framework for regime-aware market strategies.

items.name: digit-classifier
items.description: A demo project for TensorFlow. TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) framework developed by Google.

items.name: Classification-of-Heat-Related-Illness-Risk-Using-Machine-Learning-and-Explainable-AI
items.description: Designed a machine learning-based framework for the prediction of heat-related illnesses based on the analysis of environmental and physiological factors. It will help in the identification of those at risk through data inputs such as temperature, humidity, heat index, and other personal health parameters so as to give warnings for severe outcomes.

items.name: linfa
items.description: A Rust machine learning framework.

items.name: A-malware-detection-framework-for-reverse-engineered-Android-applications-using-machine-learning-alg
items.description: Designed a system to detect malware in reverse-engineered Android applications using machine learning techniques. Implemented feature extraction and classification models to enhance detection accuracy.

items.name: Mini-AI-Chatbot-Framework
items.description: Build a modular AI chatbot framework in Python that can:  Parse user input,  Choose a response using a basic machine learning model or rule-based logic,  Learn from conversations (simulated),  Support plug-and-play "skills" using OOP.

items.name: Cybersecurity-Threat-ML-Model
items.description: An advanced threat intelligence tool integrating MITRE ATT&CK framework with machine learning to prioritize cybersecurity threats and visualize attack tactics.  A machine learning-powered threat prioritization and visualization platform mapping cybersecurity data to MITRE ATT&CK techniques.

items.name: FedAverage-NjustMachineLearning
items.description: This is the machine learning final project from NJUST (Jiang Ying's class), implementing the Federated Learning framework FedAvg. All the code was written by Zijun Wang.

items.name: ML-DL-fundamentals
items.description: In this repo, I implement fundamental parts of Machine Learning and Deep Learning frameworks.

items.name: toySSL
items.description: Final Homework for Machine Learning, 2025. Toy implementation and improvement of FixMatch, which is a famous Semi-Supervised Learning framework.

items.name: Machine-Learning-Strat
items.description: A comprehensive machine learning framework for predicting S&P 500 price movements and implementing a data-driven trading strategy across multiple time horizons.

items.name: AIX
items.description: A single header Torch like C++ machine learning framework with multiple device acceleration support.

items.name: Car_Auction_Predicting
items.description: Predicting Car Auction Prices: A Machine Learning Approach Using the CRISP-DM Framework

items.name: DigitRecognizer
items.description: A machine learning-based digit recognition system that accurately identifies handwritten or printed digits from images. Built to demonstrate image processing, feature extraction, and classification techniques using popular frameworks.

items.name: AI-Fairness-Explainability-Toolkit
items.description: AI Fairness and Explainability Toolkit (AFET) is an open-source project aimed at providing tools and frameworks to assess, visualize, and mitigate bias in machine learning models. It supports multiple ML frameworks and offers a comprehensive suite of metrics and visualization components to enhance model transparency and fairness.

items.name: IMAINET
items.description: IMAINET: An Immune Algorithm-Inspired Neural Network Framework for Machine Learning

items.name: LegalizeMe
items.description: machine learning model that check legal framework

items.name: PumpkinSeeds-ML-project
items.description: An Innovative Ensemble Machine Learning  Framework for  Pumpkin Seeds Classification System using the  Forward  Sequential Minimum Redundancy  Maximum Relevance Feature Engineering

items.name: Product-Recommendation-Git
items.description: A Streamlit-Based Recommendation System is a web application that provides personalized recommendations to users using machine learning algorithms. Streamlit, a Python-based framework, allows for rapid prototyping and deployment of interactive applications with minimal coding effort.

items.name: Criminal-Behavior-Modeling-Simulation
items.description: agent-based modeling (ABM) framework for simulating criminal behavior, environmental influences, and law enforcement strategies using machine learning and advanced visualization tools.

items.name: Learning_JAX
items.description: This repository is for learning JAX a machine learning framework.

items.name: OPTIMIZED-MACHINE-LEARNING-FRAMEWORK-FOR-HEART-DISEASE-PREDICTION-
items.description: OPTIMIZED MACHINE LEARNING FRAMEWORK FOR  HEART DISEASE PREDICTION

items.name: Alzheimers-disease-prediction-and-Classification
items.description: This project is developed in machine learning using strealit framework. it has around 16,000 MRI images in dataset with three major algorithms K-Nearest Neighbor, Logistic Regression, Random Forest, with with highest accuracy of 96%.  This project classifies and predicts if the person has Alzheimers.

items.name: Predictive-and-Spatial-Analysis-of-HIVAIDS-Outcomes-in-New-York-City
items.description: A unified framework combining machine learning and spatial analysis to uncover disparities in HIV care linkage and viral suppression across NYC regions.

items.name: Data_Prep_Agent
items.description: This project preprocess an uploaded csv data file. Many kaggle challenges involve simple data preprocessing to enable further machine learning processing. This agent streamlines the process of such preprocessing and codes in a Jupyter Notebook which the user can use directly to add more machine learning frameworks.

items.name: ITEC_federated-iot-anomaly-detection
items.description: A federated learning-based IoT framework that encrypts sensor data, detects anomalies, classifies device risk levels, and visualizes blacklist data using machine learning and real-time dashboards. Intelligence trust and secure edge computing for cyber physical systems.

items.name: MOFGalaxyNet
items.description: MOFGalaxyNet aims to create a social network for Metal-Organic Frameworks (MOFs) and predict their properties using Graph Convolutional Networks (GCN). It fosters collaboration and exploration in the field of MOFs through social network analysis and machine learning.

items.name: Deep-Learning-Projects
items.description: A collection of deep learning projects implemented in Python, focusing on neural networks, computer vision, and NLP using frameworks like TensorFlow and PyTorch. Includes practical examples, datasets, and tutorials for building and evaluating advanced machine learning models.

items.name: Complete-Machine-Learning-With-Real-World-Deployment
items.description: A comprehensive guide to machine learning with Python, covering algorithms, model training, and real-world deployment using frameworks like Scikit-learn and Flask. Includes end-to-end projects with datasets and tutorials for building and deploying ML applications.

items.name: SMQTK
items.description: Python toolkit for pluggable algorithms and data structures for multimedia-based machine learning.

items.name: reductionml
items.description: Reduction-based machine learning framework with a focus on contextual bandits

items.name: ai_test_framework
items.description: AI Test Framework is a robust and flexible tool designed to simplify and streamline the testing of AI and machine learning (ML) models.

items.name: MathMorph
items.description: MathMorph is a symbolic reasoning and machine learning framework designed to generate, verify and explain novel mathematical formulas.

items.name: quantum-cnn
items.description: A novel quantum machine learning framework that combines equivariant quantum neural networks with quantum kernels for robust, symmetry-aware clustering of high-dimensional data. Demonstrated on MNIST with improved accuracy and transformation invariance.

items.name: mlx-notes
items.description: Shared personal notes created while working with the Apple MLX machine learning framework

items.name: quantum-ml-framework
items.description: A tool for quantum computing approaches to machine learning

items.name: PhishGuard-Explainable-AI-for-Phishing-Website-Detection
items.description: An advanced machine learning framework for detecting phishing websites using multiple classification models with a focus on explainability through various XAI techniques.

items.name: qnf-qaoa
items.description: Hybrid Quantum-Classical framework integrating Quantum Neural Fields (QNF) with the Quantum Approximate Optimization Algorithm (QAOA) for solving combinatorial optimization problems. Explores variational circuit design, quantum machine learning, and optimization strategies using Qiskit.

items.name: Phishing-Detection-Framework
items.description: Phishing Detection Framework is an intelligent and scalable cybersecurity solution that detects phishing URLs using a hybrid machine learning approach. It integrates deep learning, ensemble learning (XGBoost), and BBOA optimization to improve accuracy, efficiency, and robustness.

items.name: Flight-Delay-Predidction
items.description: A machine learning framework for predicting flight delays, integrating real-time weather and airport data. Uses Random Forest and XGBoost with explainability tools to uncover causal factors and provide interpretable, high-accuracy predictions for U.S. flights.

items.name: Driving_Simulator
items.description: A PyTorch based training framework for a Machine Learning Driving Simulator

items.name: langchain-introduction
items.description: Example notebooks for the 2025 course Agenti Intelligenti e Machine Learning, focusing on the LangChain framework.

items.name: mobiml
items.description: Framework for machine learning from movement data

items.name: Advanced-Ensemble-Framework-For-Malware-Detection
items.description: Advanced Ensemble Framework capable of detecting and defending against obfuscated malware threats by leveraging the combined strengths of multiple machine learning models. Our core objective is to design a robust, scalable, and adaptive detection framework that intelligently integrates static, dynamic, and behavioral analysis techniques.

items.name: Remote-Sensing-Landcover-Classification
items.description: A machine learning and deep learning-based framework for classifying remote sensing data from Landsat 5 in mountainous Colorado. Includes traditional ML models (SVM, RF, DT) and deep learning architectures (CNN, LSTM, ResNet) to classify 14 land cover types with high accuracy.

items.name: health-insurance-prediction
items.description: Machine Learning-Based Regression Framework to Predict Health Insurance Premiums

items.name: health-insurance-prediction
items.description: machine learning-based regression framework to predict health insurance premiums

items.name: Analysis-of-Demographic-and-Behavioral-Factors-in-HIV-Prediction-Using-Machine-Learning
items.description: A machine learning framework for predicting HIV status using demographic and behavioral risk factors. Tested on a dataset from high-risk populations in Bangladesh, Random Forest achieved 97.86% accuracy. Key predictors include age, STD history, drug use, and sexual orientation.

items.name: Fake-Tweet-Detection-using-Machine-Learning
items.description: Developed a machine learning framework to detect fake tweets by analyzing tweet content and using neural networks to store credibility predictions. Tackled noisy auxiliary data to build a robust, efficient system that filters fake tweets and promotes credible info.

items.name: Fruitify
items.description: Fruitify is a charming fruit recognition project that harnesses the power of TensorFlow, an advanced machine learning framework.

items.name: Realtime-Fish-Detection-GUI
items.description: It is an AI Hybrid Framework Graphical User Interface system consisting of Real-Time Underwater Fish Detection using two Machine Learning algorithms & traditional Computer Vision Algorithm and an Image Enhancement Pipeline to improve the Efficiency and Accuracy.

items.name: ML-UV-spectrum-prediction
items.description: Machine Learning framework to reproduce TDDFT UV-Vis spectra

items.name: Centrality-Metrices-and-Their-Impact-on-Loan-Outcomes-in-P2P-LEnding
items.description: A framework for analyzing P2P lending using network centrality metrics and MST-based network analysis, combined with machine learning models (XGBoost, Random Forest, Logistic Regression) to predict loan success and manage risk. Validated on real datasets for improved accuracy and scalability.

items.name: Efficient-Pediatric-Heart-Transplant-Predictions
items.description: Developed an advanced machine learning framework utilizing synthetic data generation and self-supervised learning to enhance 1-year mortality prediction in pediatric heart transplantation. Achieved up to 100% accuracy using ensemble modeling techniques.

items.name: Precision-groundwater-pollution-control-in-brownfields
items.description: A machine learning-based framework for sustainable and precision groundwater pollution management at industrial brownfields, integrating dimensionality reduction, clustering, and deep multi-view fusion of multi-source data.

items.name: Made-With-ML
items.description: This project leverages the "Made With ML" framework and resources to explore and build machine learning applications.

items.name: FedEasy
items.description: FedEasy is an intuitive powerful yet simple to use Federated Learning framework. Our goal is to streamline the process of setting up and running federated learning experiments with ease, making advanced machine learning techniques accessible to researchers and developers alike.

items.name: ICU-Risk-Predictor
items.description: A machine learning framework for ICU patient risk assessment and mortality prediction using physiological time-series data.

items.name: Multi-Emotion-Recognition-Healthcare
items.description: A multimodal machine-learning framework to enhance mental health diagnostics by analyzing audio, video, and physiological signals. This system enables early detection of depression, improves diagnostic accuracy, and supports personalized treatment, adhering to ethical and data privacy standards.

items.name: Altfit
items.description: Altfit is an advanced movement analysis framework powered by machine learning. It utilizes TensorFlow Lite models to process motion-related data, enabling applications in fitness tracking, rehabilitation, sports performance optimization, and biomechanical assessments.

items.name: Garden
items.description: This Python-based framework integrates various data analysis techniques, including statistics, deep learning, and machine learning, enabling users without coding knowledge to easily utilize them through an intuitive graphical user interface (GUI).

items.description: Code for a machine learning framework predicting antimicrobial resistance using transcriptomics, including data preprocessing and model training with Auto-sklearn.

Includes data preprocessing, multiple regression models, evaluation metrics, and visualizations.

items.name: Machine-Learning-Based-Regression-Framework-to-Predict-Health-Insurance-Premiumss
items.description: A regression-based ML framework to predict health insurance premiums using features like age, BMI, smoking status, and more. Includes data preprocessing, multiple regression models, evaluation metrics, and visualizations.

items.name: ML-With-Streamlit
items.description: This repository contains a collection of machine learning models deployed using Streamlit, a Python-based framework for building interactive web applications. The project demonstrates how to effectively integrate machine learning workflows with a user-friendly interface,making it easier for end users to interact with and understand machine learning

items.name: Blanchotian-Components-for-a-Poetics-of-Machine-Learning
items.description: Instead of treating neural networks as mechanisms for classification and certainty, this framework embraces liminality, recursion, absence, and hesitation as fundamental design principles.

items.name: Matrix
items.description: Linear algebra framework to use in machine learning

items.name: TensorFlow-in-Python
items.description: TensorFlow is an open-source machine learning framework developed by Google Brain Team.

items.name: airline-satisfaction-prediction
items.description: A school project using the CRISP-DM framework and machine learning to predict airline passenger satisfaction

items.name: iris-classifier-julia-flux
items.description: A high-performance neural network classifier for the Iris dataset implemented in Julia using the Flux machine learning framework.

items.name: ENERGY-LOAD-FORECASTING
items.description: Develop an accurate and efficient machine learning framework for predicting the heating and cooling loads of buildings. This framework aims to provide reliable energy load estimates, supporting more energy-efficient building designs and reducing overall operational costs.

items.name: kidney-rejection-predictor
items.description: Machine learning-based kidney transplant rejection prediction framework

items.name: HIT-OR-FLOP
items.description: A machine-learning framework analyzing audio features, genre, and lyrics to predict and model song popularity

items.name: Developing-a-Scalable-Machine-Learning-Framework-for-Healthcare-Analytics-Using-Snowflake-and-AWS
items.description: End-to-end machine learning framework that bridges data engineering, predictive modeling, and healthcare analytics toward data-driven decision-making.

items.name: OptimalSpectroscopicMeasurementDesign
items.description: The official code repository for "Optimal Spectroscopic Measurement Design: Bayesian Framework for Rational Data Acquisition," Machine Learning: Science and Technology 6, 025037 (2025).

items.name: Deep-Learning-and-Machine-Learning-Based-Early-Diagnosis-of-Alzheimers-from-MRI---Clinical-Data
items.description: An advanced machine learning framework for early Alzheimer's diagnosis, integrating MRI imaging with clinical data. Using a fine-tuned VGG16 CNN for brain scans and an SVM model for clinical indicators, NeuroDetect ensures precise classification, aiding researchers, neurologists, and healthcare applications in neurodegenerative disease detection.

items.name: Self-Driving-Car-JS
items.description: This project demonstrates a complete self-driving car simulation built entirely with vanilla JavaScript, without using any external libraries or machine learning frameworks.

items.name: ScaleExplorer
items.description: ScaleExplorer is a simulation framework that enables agile exploration over the large machine learning model design and optimization space. This new capability will unlock efficiency and sustainability optimization opportunities to flexibly adapt to the constantly-changing training environment.

items.name: AutoMol-v2
items.description: The AutoMol Framework is a multi-phase computational pipeline designed for the automated generation, analysis, and testing of novel molecular structures. This system integrates machine learning techniques, molecular dynamics simulations, and bioinformatics tools to create and optimize molecules tailored to specific biological functions.

items.name: heat-vulnerability-research
items.description: A machine learning-based geospatial framework for urban heat vulnerability mapping in India using high-resolution spatial, climate, and socio-economic data.

items.name: TORCS-Self-Driving-Car-AI
items.description: A Python-based framework for TORCS that enables data collection from manual driving sessions and trains AI drivers using machine learning models such as Decision Trees, Random Forests, and MLP Regressors.

items.name: Cross_Domain_Predictive_Analytics_Dashboard
items.description: An advanced web-based data platform using Python frameworks that integrates multiple data sources and applies machine learning for predictive analytics.

items.name: An-Efficient-Distributed-Machine-Learning-Inference-Framework-with-Byzantine-Fault-Detection
items.description: An Efficient Distributed Machine Learning Inference Framework with Byzantine Fault Detection

items.name: UTScan
items.description: UTScan is a hybrid machine learning framework that quantifies daily urban travel intensity using continuous seismic noise recordings. Leveraging CatBoost and LSTM, UTScan extracts features from the 2â€“20â€¯Hz seismic power spectrum to deliver accurate, generalizable travel predictions across regions and time periods.

items.name: DMAIC-Food-Delivery-Project
items.description: Analyze food delivery performance using the Lean Six Sigma DMAIC framework. Includes visual insights, control charts, and a machine learning model to predict late orders.

items.name: Infosys-Model-Inference-Library
items.description: IMIL is a versatile and powerful tool designed to simplify the deployment and utilization of machine learning models, regardless of the framework or model type.

items.name: adas
items.description: ADAS (Advanced Driving Autonomous System) is a modular, full-stack framework for building and deploying self-driving car technologies. It includes machine learning workflows, backend services, a GraphQL API, and a user-friendly frontendâ€”organized into clean, decoupled modules for flexibility and scalability.
